messages.content: Brother, you know this. I smesh everybody. This is not trash talk, this is truth.
Who the fook is that guy? I'm the double champ, I do whatever I want!
Let me tell you a story about a gangster from West Linn, Oregon. The mean streets where if you didn't drive a Mercedes, you were nobody.
Back in my day, we didn't have rounds. We had fights until someone couldn't continue. These kids today wouldn't last 5 minutes in the old days.
Conor, you tap like chicken. Everyone know this.
I'll wrap me foot around yer head faster than you can say 'tiramisu Thursday', ya dagestani rat!
I've never lost a round, never lost a fight. Anderson Silva, you absolutely suck! Oh wait, wrong chat...
You boys done with your little dance? Real men settle it in the ring with a good old-fashioned mustache and short shorts.
Don Frye, you legend brother. But short shorts time is finished. Now is smesh time.
I could buy and sell every one of ye's! My whiskey makes more money than your entire bloodlines!
Conor, I'm the biggest draw in the history of money. I've got more silver than the federal reserve.
Money talks, but a good right hand speaks volumes. And my mustache is worth more than your entire wardrobe, kid.
This is number one bullshit. Money not important. Legacy important. Father plan important.
Your da was me gardener, Khabib! I'm the king of this whole operation!
I can't let you get close! That's what I told Wanderlei Silva in a van in Portland, Oregon.
You know what? I fought Ken Shamrock with a broken hand and still looked better than all of you combined.
Send me location. Any location. Desert, mountain, street, cage. I will come.
I'm on a yacht in Dubai drinking pina coladas made with Proper 12! Come find me if ye dare!
That's cute. I once submitted an entire Brazilian crowd just by walking to the octagon.
Dubai? In my day we fought in barns and parking lots. And we liked it that way!
Brother Don Frye speak truth. Real fight not about luxury. Is about heart, is about respect.
I'll fight ye all in sequence! Line up for yer beatdowns, ya bunch of bums!
Listen Conor, I'll do you a favor and explain the difference between a threat and a fact. When I say I'll beat you, that's not a threat, that's a spoiler.
You know what your problem is, McGregor? You've never had to fight while sporting a proper mustache. It adds at least 50% more power to your punches.
Alhamdulillah, I have beard. Beard more powerful than mustache, brother Don.
I could buy and sell every mustache in the history of facial hair! And still have enough left for a proper haircut for the lot of ye!
You wanna know the difference between me and you, Conor? I can tell you exactly what happened in every fight I've lost. The problem is, there aren't any.
All this talk about money and losses... In Pride, we fought three times a night, uphill both ways, in the snow.
In Dagestan, we wrestle bear. Not for money, not for show. This is real training.
I wrestled a bear once! His name was Floyd, and he took all me money!
I once fought a bear, a lion, and a gorilla in the same night. The bear was Anderson Silva, the lion was Jon Jones, and the gorilla was Wanderlei Silva.
Bears? Try fighting Tank Abbott while wearing nothing but American flag shorts. That's patriotism and danger all rolled into one.
Tank Abbott? Brother, this man was like bear without technique. Strong, but no discipline.
I'd have knocked Tank out with me left pinky while sippin' a proper whiskey with me right!
Tank Abbott once tried to intimidate me at a bar. I told him I'm from West Linn, Oregon, where people have to share Netflix passwords. He backed down immediately.
You know what Tank's problem was? Not enough mustache. That's why he never reached his full potential.
Brother Don always talk about mustache. But have you ever try papakha? This is real power.
I'll buy every papakha in Dagestan and make a luxury line of them! Call it 'Proper Papakha' - only $999.99!
I once wore a papakha into a fight. The athletic commission tried to ban it, but I explained that I'm the biggest draw in the sport, and they apologized.
A papakha? Try wearing a cowboy hat with your mustache in Japan. The fans didn't know whether to bow or yeehaw.
Japan have respect. This is why Pride was greatest. Not like Dublin bar fight promotion.
Oi! I've had better fights in Dublin bars than your entire career! And I made more money doin' it!
Let me offer you a little something called perspective: I've had tougher fights with my alarm clock than both of you combined.
Dublin bars? Pride rings? Try fighting in a Walmart parking lot in Arizona. That's where real warriors are made.
In Dagestan, we no have Walmart. We have mountain. This is our gym.
I'll buy your mountain and turn it into a Proper 12 distillery! How'd ya like them apples?
You know what they call mountains in West Linn? Speed bumps. That's how tough we are.
Mountains? I used to climb Mount Fuji between rounds just to stay warm.
Brother Don always have good story. But nobody can beat Dagestani cardio. We train in low oxygen since birth.
Low oxygen? That's just the cheap seats where your fans sit! My fans breathe champagne air!
I once held my breath for so long, oxygen had to tap out. True story, happened twice last Tuesday.
Oxygen? In my day, we didn't need oxygen. We ran on pure testosterone and patriotism.
This is problem with new generation. Always need something. We need nothing. Only wrestling, only smesh.
I've got a new energy drink coming out! It's just Proper 12 with Red Bull in it! Patent pending!
Energy drinks? I just bottle my post-fight interviews. One sip and you'll be undefeated for life.
The only energy drink you need is a shot of Wild Turkey and the American national anthem.
Brother, alcohol is haram. Better to drink borjomi water. Make you strong like bear.
I'll buy your entire borjomi supply and turn it into Proper 12 mixer! Everything is business!
You know what they call borjomi in West Linn? Nothing, because we're too tough for water.
Water? Back in my day, we rehydrated with pure adrenaline squeezed from our opponents' fear.
This is why you are legend, Don Frye. You understand old school way. Respect.
Old school? I'm the new school, the business school, and the fashion school all rolled into one!
I'm so old school, I taught the old school how to be old school. Ask Wanderlei Silva, if he ever learns English.
Fashion school? Son, my mustache has more fight experience than your entire wardrobe.
When father teach me wrestling, he say fashion is distraction. Only need papakha and respect.
I respect money, and money respects my suits! That's the only relationship ya need!
I wore a suit made of pure confidence once. The athletic commission banned it for being too powerful.
Suits? My American flag shorts have more dignity than an entire Men's Warehouse.
We need make training session. No suits, no money talk. Only wrestling. I show you father plan.
I'll livestream it and charge PPV! We'll call it 'The Money Channel'!
The only plan you need is the Chael P. Sonnen success plan. Step 1: Be Chael P. Sonnen. There is no step 2.
Training session? Let's do it old school: no rules, no refs, just mustaches and mayhem.
First rule of training: no Irish whiskey allowed. This is serious business, brother.
No whiskey?! That's discrimination against the Irish! I'll sue ya with me Proper 12 lawyers!
I once sued myself and won. The judge was so impressed, he retired on the spot.
Lawyers? In Pride, we settled everything with push-ups and protein shakes.
This is way. No court, no lawyer. Only gym, only respect, only smesh.
I'm starting me own court system! The judge's robe will be made of pure gold!
I don't need a court system. I am the law in West Linn, Oregon. Just ask my neighbor's gardener's cousin.
The only law you need is the law of the mustache. It's never wrong and always fair.
You know what real court is? Wrestling mat. No appeal process.
I'll buy every wrestling mat in the world and replace them with Proper 12 branded octagons!
In West Linn, we don't need wrestling mats. We wrestle on broken glass and expired credit cards.
Wrestling mats? Try grappling on the deck of an aircraft carrier during a typhoon. That's how we trained in my day.
Brother Don always have crazy story. But in mountain, we wrestle on snow. Nature is best mat.
Snow? I'll turn yer mountain into a winter resort! Proper 12 Snow Lodge, only $10,000 a night!
I once made it snow in Brazil just by cutting a promo. True story, ask Anderson Silva.
Snow resort? Back in Pride, we fought in volcanoes. The lava kept us honest.
This is why Pride never die in heart. Real warrior mentality.
Pride? I'll buy the rights and rename it 'Proper Pride'! Everything's for sale!
Pride? I offered to buy it with the loose change in my couch, but they said that was too much money.
You can't buy Pride, son. Pride is in the mustache, and the mustache is forever.
Brother, you speak truth. Money cannot buy respect. Cannot buy legacy.
I'll buy respect! I'll buy legacy! I'll buy the whole dictionary if I have to!
I wrote the dictionary. Every word in it is just a different way to spell 'undefeated and undisputed'.
The only dictionary you need is the Encyclopedia of Pain, written by my right hand.
Pain is temporary. Father plan is forever. This is what dictionary cannot teach.
I'll write me own book! 'How to Make Money by Being Proper Rich' - Chapter 1: Buy Proper 12!
My autobiography made the New York Times Best Seller list before I even wrote it.
Books? My mustache tells better stories than any book ever written.
In Dagestan, we no need book. Mountain teach everything you need know.
I'll buy yer mountain and turn it into a library! All books about me success!
Libraries in West Linn only stock one book: 'The Art of Being the Bad Guy' by yours truly.
The only reading material you need is the Constitution and a protein shake label.
Send location of library. I come there, teach real lesson about humility.
The library's in me yacht! Admission is just 12 bottles of Proper 12!
I once checked out every book in a library. They gave me a late fee, so I bought the library.
Library on a yacht? Try reading while fighting Ken Shamrock in a tornado. That's multitasking.
Ken Shamrock was legend. But he never fight Dagestani winter. This is different level.
Winter? I'll heat the whole of Dagestan with Proper 12 bonfires! Keep ye all warm!
I once made it snow in Brazil just by cutting a promo. True story, ask Anderson Silva.
You know what keeps you warm in winter? American flag shorts and a championship mindset.
Championship mindset come from humble beginning. Not from shorts or whiskey.
Humble? I started with nothin' and now I own half of Dublin! That's proper humble!
I'm so humble, I let other fighters win sometimes. Just kidding, I've never lost.
Want humble? Try fighting in Japan where they bow before they try to kick your head off.
Japan and Dagestan same spirit. Respect first, then smesh.
I respect money, and money respects me! That's all the spirit ye need!
The only spirit I know is the American Spirit, and it's undefeated just like me.
Spirit? My mustache has more spirit than all your bank accounts combined.
Bank account mean nothing in cage. Only heart matter.
Me heart's made of gold! Proper 12 karat gold!
I donated my heart to science. They said it was too powerful to study.
Heart? Try having a heart-to-heart with Bas Rutten in a dark alley. That's cardiac training.
Bas Rutten also legend. But he never wrestle eagle on mountain top.
Eagles? I own a fleet of private jets! That's proper flying!
I once flew without a plane. The FAA tried to fine me, but I explained I'm from West Linn.
Private jets? In my day, we parachuted into the ring from military helicopters.
This is problem. Too much show, no substance. Real fighter need only wrestling shoes.
I'll make wrestling shoes with gold soles! Only a million per pair!
I wrestled barefoot once. The mat asked for my autograph.
Wrestling shoes? Real men fight in cowboy boots and still throw head kicks.
Head kick good, but ground game better. Father teach this first day.
I'll buy the ground and put me name on it! McGregor Terrain™, only $999 per square foot!
The ground is afraid to touch me. That's why I float three inches above it at all times.
Ground game? Back in my day, we fought on hot coals while reciting the Pledge of Allegiance.
This is why you legend, brother Don. Always bring patriotism to fight game.
Patriotism? I'll paint the Irish flag with pure gold! That's proper patriotism!
I am so patriotic, bald eagles ask for my autograph. True story, happened yesterday.
My mustache once made the entire Japanese audience stand for the Star-Spangled Banner.
In Dagestan, we no need anthem. Mountain wind is our music.
I'll buy yer mountain wind and bottle it! Proper Air™ - breathe like a champion!
I once bottled my own swagger. The FDA banned it for being too potent.
Bottled air? Try breathing pure testosterone and victory. That's what my mustache filters.
Victory not come from bottle. Come from hard work, come from discipline.
I'll put discipline in a bottle! Proper Discipline™ - only $500 per sip!
I trademarked discipline before it was invented. The patent office still owes me royalties.
Discipline? Try growing this mustache while fighting in a tornado. That's discipline.
Tornado is nothing. Try wrestling bear in snowstorm while father watch.
I'll buy all the bears and train them to sell Proper 12! Business genius!
Bears? I arm-wrestled a grizzly in West Linn. He now works as my accountant.
Bears respect the mustache. It's nature's law.
Nature have many law. Most important is smesh everything.
I'll copyright the word 'smesh' and charge ye royalties! Proper Business™!
I invented smashing before smashing was cool. Ask Anderson Silva's ego.
Smashing? My mustache once KO'd three guys just by twitching.
Brother Don mustache is like Dagestani beard. Full of power, full of wisdom.
I'll start a premium beard oil company! Proper Facial Hair™ - only $200 per drop!
My facial hair grows so fast, barbers pay me to stay away. True story, happened this morning.
Beard oil? Real men use a mixture of victory and testosterone as aftershave.
Victory best cologne. Defeat worst perfume. This is what father always say.
I'm launching a new fragrance! Eau de Proper™ - smells like money and gold!
My natural scent is so powerful, it's classified as a controlled substance in 48 states.
The only cologne a real man needs is the smell of freedom and a well-maintained mustache.
In mountain, only smell is victory and fear of bear. This is natural perfume.
Fear of bear? I'll bottle that too! Proper Fear™ - make yer opponents run!
Fear is afraid of me. It sends me Christmas cards apologizing for existing.
Fear? My mustache eats fear for breakfast, with a side of concrete.
Breakfast most important meal. In Dagestan, we eat mountain lion eggs.
I'll start a breakfast cereal! Proper O's™ - made with real gold flakes!
I eat black belts for breakfast. The leather is rich in protein.
Real breakfast? Raw eggs, gunpowder, and the American dream.
American dream good, but Dagestani reality better. We dream while smashing.
Dreams? I'll sell ye dreams in a bottle! Proper Dreams™ - now with gold sparkles!
My dreams are so intense, they keep other people awake. Ask Tito Ortiz.
Dreams? My mustache doesn't sleep. It stands guard over America.
Sleep is for lightweight. Heavyweight never sleep, only train.
I'll make a luxury mattress filled with money! Proper Rest™ - sleep like a billionaire!
I don't sleep, I wait. The Sandman still owes me money from our last fight.
Sleep? In Pride, we just took power naps between rounds while doing push-ups.
Push-up good exercise. But wrestling bear better cardio.
I'm opening a chain of gold-plated gyms! Proper Fitness™ - where the dumbbells are made of diamonds!
My workout routine is so intense, gravity takes a break when I train.
Gyms? We lifted engine blocks and wrestled buffalo. That's real CrossFit.
CrossFit? Brother, try carrying father up mountain every morning. This is workout.
I'll buy the mountain and install golden escalators! Proper Mountain™!
Mountains bow down when I approach. That's why Oregon is so flat.
Real mountains? Try climbing the stack of guys I knocked out. That's elevation training.
Elevation good for lungs. But pressure of father plan better for heart.
I'll make a fitness app! Proper Training™ - each workout costs a thousand euros!
My training app just shows videos of me talking. It's undefeated in the App Store.
Apps? My mustache has its own workout video. It's rated too intense for public release.
Video cannot teach real fighting. Only father plan can teach.
I'll film me father plan! Proper Parenting™ - only $999 per lesson!
My father's plan was so good, other plans had to get restraining orders.
Father plan? My mustache raised three generations of fighters by itself.
This is why you legend, brother Don. Mustache have wisdom of many generations.
I'll start a mustache academy! Proper Facial Academy™ - where every hair is insured!
My facial hair insurance policy is thicker than the Bible. True story, ask Jesus.
Insurance? My mustache is its own insurance policy. Backed by pure American grit.
Only insurance we need in Dagestan is wrestling skill. Always protect you.
I'll insure yer whole country! Proper Protection™ - premium rates in solid gold!
I tried to get insurance once, but they said I was too much of a risk to the laws of physics.
The only insurance you need is a strong mustache and an American flag bandana.
Brother Don speak wisdom again. Simple life is best life.
Simple? I'll make simple expensive! Proper Simplicity™ - only the richest can afford it!
I'm so simple, complexity had to file for bankruptcy. Ask Wall Street.
Simplicity is an American flag, a good mustache, and the will to win.
